Purpose:

This folder holds the data models or entities in the app. These are Kotlin data classes or classes
annotated with @Entity for Room or any ORM (Object Relational Mapping) framework.
These models represent the structure of your database tables or other data forms.

What to include:

* Kotlin data classes
* Room @Entity annotated classes
* Other model objects like API response models

Examples:

* User.kt
* Inventory.kt
* Product.kt

== Example [Inventory.kt] ==
    // imports: Uses room (Entity, PK) for local database and java.io (Serializable)
    @Entity
    data class Inventory(
        @PrimaryKey(autoGenerate = true)
        val id: Int = 0,
        val name: String,
        val price: Int,
        val quantity: Int): Serializable

== Example [Product.kt] ==
    // imports: Uses room (Entity, PK) for local database and java.io (Serializable)
    data class Product(
        @SerializedName("id")
        val id:Int,

        @SerializedName("title")
        val title: String,

        @SerializedName("image")
        val image:String
    )